---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/page/PageHero.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms | Virtual Ventures"
  description="Plain English terms for using Virtual Ventures pages, patterns, links, videos and shop notes."
  showFooterBreadcrumbs={false}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Site Notes"
    title="Terms"
    description="Clear workshop rules for using the Virtual Ventures website, patterns, downloads, links and community support."
  />

  <main class="page-shell">
    <section class="page-intro">
      <p class="eyebrow">Website terms</p>
      <h1>Kind rules, firm edges</h1>
      <p>
        These terms are draft website wording for review before publishing. They
        are here to help visitors understand how Virtual Ventures content can be
        used.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Using this website</h2>
        <p>
          You are welcome to read the blog, browse the gallery, use free pattern
          pages on the website, share links, and use the site for personal craft
          learning and inspiration.
        </p>
        <p>
          Please do not attack the site, scrape it in bulk, copy large sections
          into another database, pretend Virtual Ventures content is yours, or
          use the site in a way that harms the workshop or other visitors.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Patterns and downloads</h2>
        <p>
          Free pattern pages are free to read and use on the Virtual Ventures
          website, but they are still copyrighted. Free does not mean public
          domain.
        </p>
        <p>
          Optional printable PDFs on Etsy and future printed KDP collections are
          support purchases for people who prefer a polished printable or
          physical copy. They do not remove the copyright from the original
          pattern, photos, layout or files.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Shop and platform purchases</h2>
        <p>
          Virtual Ventures may link to Etsy for optional PDF pattern purchases
          and to Amazon or KDP for future printed collections. Those purchases
          are handled by the platform you buy from.
        </p>
        <p>
          Please check the platform page, delivery information, download access,
          refund rules and account settings before buying. Virtual Ventures does
          not control Etsy, Amazon, KDP, YouTube or social platform rules.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Videos and livestreams</h2>
        <p>
          Stitch videos, livestream replays and Crochet and Chatter sessions are
          support and learning materials. They are not a promise that every
          person will get the same result first time.
        </p>
        <p>
          Crochet involves tension, yarn choice, hook size, stuffing, sewing,
          frogging and tiny decisions along the way. Please pause, replay, ask
          questions where available, and check the latest pattern version on the
          website.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Safety and suitability</h2>
        <p>
          Patterns, tutorials and examples are for craft learning. Finished items
          may need extra safety checks, especially if they include safety eyes,
          buttons, beads, wire, stuffing, small parts, long cords or anything
          that could become loose.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unless a finished item is clearly sold as a tested toy by Virtual
          Ventures, do not assume it is suitable for babies, children or pets.
          Makers selling finished items are responsible for their own safety
          checks, labels, local rules and customer information.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Changes and corrections</h2>
        <p>
          Virtual Ventures may update website pages, pattern wording, stitch
          explanations, photos, links, QR codes, prices, availability and policy
          pages over time.
        </p>
        <p>
          Official corrections and current versions should live on the Virtual
          Ventures website, so pattern IDs and verification links can point
          people back to the trusted source.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-closing-card">
      <p>
        These terms should be reviewed before the first live contact form,
        newsletter, paid digital download, kit, toy sale or supporter video goes
        live.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
